From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Thu, 5 Feb 2026 23:10:04 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] drm: cix: dptx: Fix hotplug state machine on repeated resets

When a display is unplugged but the system continues requesting output,
repeated DP resets can cause loss of HDMI signal and missed HPD events.

Fix the state machine:
- Clear DP_STATE_INIT_TRAIN in core_off to prevent repeated resets
- Add delay after reset_dp_and_reinit for hardware settling
- Check both INITIALIZED and READY states before enabling output
- Change error to warning for transient not-ready states
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c | 12 +++++++-----
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
index 93d0cf511749e..e4668c67bdcf6 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
@@ -2148,6 +2148,7 @@ static int trilin_dp_core_off(struct trilin_dp *dp)
 			0, sizeof(struct trilin_dp_mst_ch_slot_info) * dp->max_streams);
 
 	dp->state &= ~DP_STATE_READY;
+	dp->state &= ~DP_STATE_INIT_TRAIN;
 
 	return rc;
 }
@@ -2975,7 +2976,8 @@ int trilin_dp_prepare(struct trilin_dp *dp)
 			goto end;
 		}
 	} else if (dp->state & DP_STATE_INIT_TRAIN){
-		reset_dp_and_reinit(dp); //enable dp reset...
+		reset_dp_and_reinit(dp);
+		usleep_range(100, 200);
 	}
 
 	if (!trilin_dp_is_ready(dp)) {
@@ -2996,11 +2998,11 @@ int trilin_dp_enable(struct trilin_dp *dp, struct trilin_dp_panel *dp_panel)
 	DP_DEBUG("enter\n");
 	mutex_lock(&dp->session_lock);
 	/*
-	 * If DP_STATE_INITIALIZED is not set, we should not do any HW
-	 * programming.
+	 * If DP_STATE_INITIALIZED or DP_STATE_READY is not set, we should
+	 * not do any HW programming.
 	 */
-	if (!(dp->state & DP_STATE_INITIALIZED)) {
-		DP_ERR("[host not ready]");
+	if (!(dp->state & DP_STATE_INITIALIZED) || !(dp->state & DP_STATE_READY)) {
+		DP_WARN("[host not ready]");
 		goto end;
 	}
 
